Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Dice @Sweet Potatoes{1} into ½-inch pieces. (TIP: Feel free to peel first if you
like.) Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon},
@Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.
(You'll use the rest of the BBQ Seasoning later.)

Roast on middle rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and lightly
browned, ~{20-25%minutes}. Let cool at least ~{5%minutes} after removing from
oven.

While sweet potato roasts, halve and core @Apple{1}; quarter halves lengthwise,
then thinly slice crosswise into triangles.

Place @Pecans{½%ounce} in a #medium pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium
heat. Toast, shaking pan frequently, until fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; remove pecans from pan.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
remaining @Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for pecans over medium
heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}
per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @Mixed Greens{2%ounce}, apple, and roasted sweet potato
with @Honey Dijon Dressing{1.5%ounce} to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide salad between bowls and top with sliced chicken. Garnish with toasted
pecans and serve.

> Step aside, side salad—these mixed greens are main dish material. Hearty
> elements like BBQ-spiced chicken, toasted pecans, and tender roasted sweet
> potato are balanced by a tangy honey Dijon dressing and crisp, sweet bites of
> fresh apple for a light, yet super-satisfying, bowl. Now, what if we told you
> that could all be on your table in just 25 minutes? Talk about a dinner dream
> come true!